Description of the hemipenis (
Fig. 5
). Bilobed, with no capitulum or ornamentations but with a wrinkled surface. Lobes correspond to about one third of hemipenial body, with simple rounded tips slightly curved towards the asulcate side. Sulcus spermaticus with prominent lips bifurcates at the base of the lobes, each branch following to the tip of a lobe in a centrolineal direction. On the asulcate side a dense semi-circle of inner tissue is well visible by transparency at the branching point of the organ projecting inside both lobes.
